## Acceptable Use

You are responsible for your use of the software, including everything an agent,
experiment, suite, scoring code, or other author- or agent-supplied code does when you
run it — locally, over a network, or against any third-party or upstream system. You must
ensure that your use, and any activity you cause through the software, complies with all
applicable laws and with the terms, acceptable-use policies, and rate limits of every
third-party service it touches (including model and tool providers). The software executes
author-supplied and agent-generated code with open network access by design; see the Trust
Model (docs/TRUST_MODEL.md). The Licensor does not monitor, control, direct, or approve
what you run or what your runs do.

## Costs and Third-Party Services

The software can make, or cause an agent to make, calls to paid third-party services (for
example, model-provider APIs) using credentials that you supply. **You are solely
responsible for all charges, fees, and obligations you incur with those services.** The
software does not impose any spend, token, or usage cap: a run is bounded by its configured
timeout and by the agent's own behavior, not by a monetary or token budget, and a
malfunctioning, looping, or adversarial agent may incur substantial charges within that
window. Any cost figures the software reports are after-the-fact estimates computed from
captured traffic; they are not billing, are not authoritative, and do not limit anything.
You are responsible for bounding your own spend (for example, with provider-side budgets
and rate limits and with scoped, low-limit credentials). As stated in "No Liability" above,
the Licensor is not liable to you for any such charges.

